:GRAPH WIP_CASH_REV
:TITLE Retains Cash Revenue
:WIP
:X-MIN 0
:X-MAX 60
:SCALE
:VAR RETAINED CASH FLOW
:Y-MIN 0
:Y-MAX 40000
:DATASET BASE
:VAR RETAINED CASH FLOW
:DATASET 
:VAR RETAINED CASH FLOW
:DATASET *2
:VAR RETAINED CASH FLOW
:DATASET *3

:GRAPH BASE_V_ACTUAL
:TITLE Base Run Versus Available Data
:SCALE
:VAR cash revenue|Revenue in base run
:Y-MIN 0
:Y-MAX 500000
:DATASET base
:VAR cash revenue|.......................actual
:DATASET market
:SCALE
:VAR fraction custs buying|Marketing effectiveness in base
:Y-MIN 0
:Y-MAX 1
:DATASET base
:VAR fraction custs buying|.....................................actual
:DATASET market

:GRAPH DATA_AND_BEST
:TITLE Optimized Run Versus Available Data
:SCALE
:VAR cash_revenue|Revenue in optimized run
:DATASET calibrate.vdf
:VAR cash_revenue|..................... actual
:DATASET market.vdf
:SCALE
:VAR fraction_custs_buying|Marketing effectiveness in optimized
:DATASET calibrate.vdf
:VAR fraction_custs_buying|....................................... actual
:DATASET market.vdf

:GRAPH RETAINED_CASH
:TITLE Perfomance Before and After Policy Optimization
:SCALE
:VAR retained_cash_flow|Retained earnings before
:DATASET calibrat.vdf
:VAR retained_cash_flow|...................after
:UNITS Dollars/Month
:DATASET optimal.vdf
:SCALE
:VAR cash_revenue|Revenue before
:Y-MAX 800000
:DATASET calibrat.vdf
:VAR cash_revenue|..............after
:UNITS $/Month
:Y-MAX 800000
:DATASET optimal.vdf

:GRAPH MARKET_EFF
:TITLE Market Effectiveness in Model Relative to Data
:X-LABEL Months since January 1, 1985
:X-MIN 12
:SCALE
:VAR fraction_custs_buying|Model Results
:DATASET best.vdf
:VAR fraction_custs_buying|Actual Data
:UNITS Fraction
:Y-MIN 0.45
:Y-MAX 0.55
:DATASET market.vdf

:REPORT COMM1
:TITLE COMM1
:LOCATION -1,-1
:SIZE -1,-1
:FONT Times New Roman|10||0-0-0
The software allows you to explore a model through a number of menus
and output screens.  To select a menu item you can click on it, type the
first letter in the menu description or select it using the up and down
arrow keys and then press the enter key.  The selected menu item appears 
highlighted - usually black on white.  In some cases buttons are used in
place of menu items.  To activate these click on them.

Additional functionality available in the software is described in 
places where it can be used.  To conserve space, later commentaries
will be kept small, and you will need to scroll them to read all the
information they contain.
:END-OF-REPORT

:REPORT COMM4
:TITLE COMM4
:LOCATION -1,-1
:SIZE -1,-1
:FONT Times New Roman|10||0-0-0
The cause and use screens show lists of
different variables.  The graphs allows
you to compare different scenarios.
The trees allow you to investigate the
structure of the model.

You can double click on a variable name
in the graphs, trees or documentation to
view the same analysis screen for that
variable.  You can also use the S
command to select a new variable to work
with.

You can print the contents of the graphs
and trees using the P command.  Output
will be directed to your default printer.

During causal tracing you can switch
between the Tree and Graph represen-
tations of causes.  This can be
useful as means of understanding both
structure and behavior.
:END-OF-REPORT

